Activation Targets

An activation target is the location, including authentication and authorization information, where a segment’s data is being sent during activation (for example, Marketing Cloud Engagement). You can create, edit, and delete activation targets.

Create a File Storage Activation Target
Create an activation target in Data Cloud to publish segments to file storage activation platforms such as Amazon S3, SFTP, Google Cloud Storage (GCS), and Microsoft Azure blob storage.
Create an External Activation Target in Data Cloud
To publish segments to your external platform account, create an activation target. An external platform can have multiple activation targets, but you can attach only one activation target to an external platform account.
Create a Marketing Cloud Engagement Activation Target
To publish segments to Marketing Cloud Engagement business units, create an activation target in Data Cloud.
Create a Data Cloud Loyalty Activation Target
To publish segments for use with Loyalty Cloud, create an activation target in Data Cloud. You can create one activation target for Salesforce.
Create a Data Cloud Activation Target
Create an activation target in Data Cloud to publish segments to the Audience DMO. You can access data from segments without a direct connection to an internal or external target system by publishing the data to the Audience DMO. You can then retrieve the data using Query APIs, similar to querying any other DMO.
Create a B2C Commerce Activation Target
To publish segments to Commerce Cloud, create an activation target in Data Cloud.
Create a Marketing Cloud Personalization Activation Target
To publish segments to Marketing Cloud Personalization (formerly Interaction Studio), create an activation target in Data Cloud.
Delete Activation Targets
If an activation target is no longer needed, it can be deleted through Data Cloud Activation Targets. The deletion of an activation target applies to all segments using the activation target.
Disable and Enable Activation Targets
When an activation target is ready for use in activation, enable it through Data Cloud Activation Targets. To temporarily remove access in Activation, disable the activation target.
